<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ilicis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ilicis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ilicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. This group was recently revised in North America by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1603/AN11008" author="Lonsdale, O" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Entomological Society of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1183 - 1206" refId="B145" refString="Lonsdale, O, Scheffer, SJ, 2011. Revision of the Holly leaf-miners in the Nearctic (Phytomyza: Agromyzidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America 104 (6): 1183 - 1206, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1603/AN11008" title="Revision of the Holly leaf-miners in the Nearctic (Phytomyza: Agromyzidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1603/AN11008" volume="104" year="2011">Lonsdale and Scheffer (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, who included discussions on life history and host use. This followed molecular treatments of the group by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1006/mpev.2000.0830" author="Scheffer, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="244 - 255" refId="B221" refString="Scheffer, SJ, Wiegmann, BM, 2000. Molecular phylogenetics of the holly leafminers (Diptera: Agromyzidae: Phytomyza): Species limits, speciation and dietary specialization. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 17: 244 - 255, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1006/mpev.2000.0830" title="Molecular phylogenetics of the holly leafminers (Diptera: Agromyzidae: Phytomyza): Species limits, speciation and dietary specialization." url="https://doi.org/10.1006/mpev.2000.0830" volume="17" year="2000">Scheffer and Wiegmann (2000)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-294X.2007.03303.x" author="Scheffer, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Ecology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="2627 - 2637" refId="B216" refString="Scheffer, SJ, Hawthorne, DJ, 2007. Molecular evidence of host-associated genetic divergence in the holly leafminer Phytomyza glabricola (Diptera: Agromyzidae): Apparent discordance among marker systems. Molecular Ecology 16: 2627 - 2637, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-294X.2007.03303.x" title="Molecular evidence of host-associated genetic divergence in the holly leafminer Phytomyza glabricola (Diptera: Agromyzidae): Apparent discordance among marker systems." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-294X.2007.03303.x" volume="16" year="2007">Scheffer and Hawthorne (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, and the description of a related species feeding on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.L.Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gelsemiaceae" genus="Gelsemium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gelsemium" order="Rubiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gelsemium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.L.Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gelsemiaceae" genus="Gelsemium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rubiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="family">Gelsemiaceae</taxonomicName>
) in North Carolina, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. omlandi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="omlandi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. omlandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scheffer and Lonsdale (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.4289/0013-8797.113.1.42" author="Scheffer, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="42 - 49" refId="B219" refString="Scheffer, SJ, Lonsdale, O, 2011. Phytomyza omlandi spec. nov. - The first species of Agromyzidae (Diptera: Schizophora) reared from the family Gelsemiaceae (Asteridae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 113 (1): 42 - 49, DOI: https://doi.org/10.4289/0013-8797.113.1.42" title="Phytomyza omlandi spec. nov. - The first species of Agromyzidae (Diptera: Schizophora) reared from the family Gelsemiaceae (Asteridae)." url="https://doi.org/10.4289/0013-8797.113.1.42" volume="113" year="2011">Scheffer and Lonsdale 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/aesa/saaa034" author="Scheffer, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Entomological Society of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="59 - 69" refId="B218" refString="Scheffer, SJ, Lewis, ML, Hebert, JB, Jacobsen, F, 2021. Diversity and Host Plant-Use in North American Phytomyza Holly Leafminers (Diptera: Agromyzidae): Colonization, Divergence, and Specificity in a Host-Associated Radiation. Annals of the Entomological Society of America 114 (1): 59 - 69, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/aesa/saaa034" title="Diversity and Host Plant-Use in North American Phytomyza Holly Leafminers (Diptera: Agromyzidae): Colonization, Divergence, and Specificity in a Host-Associated Radiation." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/aesa/saaa034" volume="114" year="2021">Scheffer et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
provided a thorough analysis of the host plant use and diversification in the group. Of the 12 Nearctic species in this group, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ilicis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ilicis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ilicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was introduced into the western Nearctic from Europe and eleven native species occur in the eastern United States. An additional undescribed species from Florida and North Carolina mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1093/aesa/saaa034" author="Scheffer, SJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Entomological Society of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="59 - 69" refId="B218" refString="Scheffer, SJ, Lewis, ML, Hebert, JB, Jacobsen, F, 2021. Diversity and Host Plant-Use in North American Phytomyza Holly Leafminers (Diptera: Agromyzidae): Colonization, Divergence, and Specificity in a Host-Associated Radiation. Annals of the Entomological Society of America 114 (1): 59 - 69, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1093/aesa/saaa034" title="Diversity and Host Plant-Use in North American Phytomyza Holly Leafminers (Diptera: Agromyzidae): Colonization, Divergence, and Specificity in a Host-Associated Radiation." url="https://doi.org/10.1093/aesa/saaa034" volume="114" year="2021">Scheffer et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Ilex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ilex amelanchier" order="Aquifoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amelanchier">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ilex amelanchier</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not considered here. Nine of the eleven described native species occur in the Delmarva states: 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ditmani" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ditmani">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ditmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. glabricola" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="glabricola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. glabricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ilicicola" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="ilicicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. ilicicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. leslieae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="leslieae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. leslieae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. lineata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="lineata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. lineata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. nemopanthi" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nemopanthi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. nemopanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. opacae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="opacae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. opacae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. verticillatae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="verticillatae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. verticillatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. wiggii" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="wiggii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. wiggii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species group is tentatively treated as monophyletic on the basis of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aquifoliaceae" genus="Ilex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ilex" order="Aquifoliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ilex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-feeding, widely separated posterior ocelli, and overall genitalic morphology. The eleven native Nearctic species are further allied on the basis of a subrectangular ocellar tubercle and a bump above the anus on the epandrium (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1603/AN11008" author="Lonsdale, O" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Entomological Society of America" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1183 - 1206" refId="B145" refString="Lonsdale, O, Scheffer, SJ, 2011. Revision of the Holly leaf-miners in the Nearctic (Phytomyza: Agromyzidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America 104 (6): 1183 - 1206, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1603/AN11008" title="Revision of the Holly leaf-miners in the Nearctic (Phytomyza: Agromyzidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1603/AN11008" volume="104" year="2011">Lonsdale and Scheffer 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
